class Solution {
    public long waysToBuyPensPencils(int total, int cost1, int cost2) {
        long ways = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i * cost1 <= total; i++) {
            int remaining = total - i * cost1;
            ways += (remaining / cost2) + 1;
        }
        return ways;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(total / cost1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a single loop to iterate over the possible number of pens, and for each iteration, it calculates the remaining amount of money that can be spent on pencils. The number of ways to buy pencils is then calculated as the remaining amount divided by the cost of a pencil, plus one (for the case where no pencils are bought).

